###

The usual readiness probes and liveness probes.

If the wm is not ready it will be removed by the ep of a svc so it does not receice traffic. 

The liveness is the same but when the vm is already running and it fails it gets removed from the ep behing the svc.

THe usual properties: 
- initialDelaySeconds;
- periodSeconds;
- timeoutSeconds; 
- failureThreshold;
- successThreshold. 


The probes you can do are: httpGet o exec. But also but less used tcpSocket and grpc

httpGet    -> controllo HTTP
exec       -> comando nel container
tcpSocket  -> porta TCP aperta
grpc       -> health check gRPC, se l'app lo supporta

When you set the probes to the vm, you have to restart them, do not forget that!


### Example

readinessProbe:
  tcpSocket:
    port: 5432